.subsubsection  Using the Wizard
During the package installation you will have been prompted to type in a password for the easygp user, here I am the user 'RT' but you should type in the user name 'easygp' and whatever password you gave this user during the setup. In the worked environment, you must put in the network address first as shown in the second dialog pictured here:

.image gettingstarted/logon_dialogs.png


You will then be presented with the first page of the wizard which tells you a little about EasyGP itself and its limitations.

.image gettingstarted/setupwizard-page-welcome.png

In particuliar you should note the emphasis that EasyGP cannot be guaranteed to be bug free and that the user of the program must accept full responsiblity for their clinical decisions, including verifying the accurary of drug allergies and interactions and all decision suppport software tools, and not assume that this software will be 100% accurate.If you do notice any inaccuracies it would be helpful to notify the authors.

After reading this there are a number of steps to complete, some of which will be described in more detail in this help fiile:

.item About the licence and specific disclaimers
.item Read and accept the licence agreement
.item Notes on installation options
.item Entering your practice details
.item Creating a system administrator
.item Reviewing your configuration
.item Save your configuration
.item Running EasyGP for the first time

.subsubsection  Disclaimers & Warrenty Limitations
.image gettingstarted/setupwizard-page-warrenty-disclaimers.png

You should carefully read this page. If you do not accept the warrenty and understand and accept the disclaimers you should remove EasyGP from your computer and not proceed with the installation


.subsubsection  Licence Agreement
.image gettingstarted/setupwizard-page-accept-gnu-licence.png

You should read the entire text of the licence properly and understand it as you are legally 
obliged to adhere to this licence once you have clicked the accept licence checkupbox and 
installed the software.


.subsubsection  Your Practice Details
.imagetext gettingstarted/setupwizard-page-practice-details.png
.end imagetext


In this section you should enter the name of the head office or your organisation
usually this will be the general practice you work in, the category would usually be 'General Practice'. The setup wizard will also assist you by popping up lists of suburbs, and generally prompting 
you for missing information.

.subsubsection  Adding An Admin User
.image gettingstarted/setupwizard-page-adding-admin-user.png

The system administrator should be a trusted member of your staff and should have 
a reasonable knowledge of Information Technology and using computer programs as they 
will be given access rights to all modules and database functions. 

.subsubsection  Previewing your setup
.imagetext gettingstarted/setupwizard-page-summary.png
.end imagetext

You will be presented with a summary of the information you have entered.

This page is the last chance to either go back and change what you are not happy about, or 
to cancel the wizard.
 
Once you click the 'Next' button, the data from the wizard will be written to the database and you will instructed to logon to your new database as the user you have just entered in the wizard.

